    "attributes": {
        "action": "Fund information campaign for secondary school teachers about generative AI",
        "additional_details": "We think secondary schools using AI images in powerpoints, using AI prompts and encouraging its usage is unnecessary and incites laziness and hinders students\u2019 development of key life skills such as creativity and summarizing information (which is important for revision). Discouraging its use among teachers and subsequently students motivates independent thinking and fosters necessary competence.",
        "background": "The government should educate secondary school teachers during their training courses on the pitfalls and risks of encouraging their students to use AI when it isn\u2019t necessary (creative assignments, revision, etc) by setting an example.",
